    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-06-12T16:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-06-12T16:00:00-05:00" n="471"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d471">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">835.741/37: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Argentina</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Armour</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Buenos Aires</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-06-12T18:00:00-03:00"
                            >June 12, 1943—6 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received June 12—5:20 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1318. My 1309, 11th. I am informed that the decree prohibiting use of code in
                    international radio communications is now being enforced and is applied to both
                    incoming and outgoing traffic.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Armour</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
